		<td><b>Switching from Gentoo to Ubuntu</b></td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />Hey all. I've been seriously considering switching my webserver/email-server/blog/router/CVS-server/bugzilla/etc/etc machine from gentoo to ubuntu.
<br />
<br />I started learning linux on gentoo a loooooooong time ago.  And talk about diving headfirst into linux - dang!  But I did learn a ton...but now I'm just tired of having to compile everything when I want to upgrade the system and also having to deal with all the dependency issues of portage (i.e. gentoo's package manager).  I think it would be nice to have a much more user-friendly upgrade and package install process from this point forward.  Gentoo is just too much of a maintenance hassle and manual/tedious labor process as far as I'm concerned.
<br />
<br />Anyone have any thoughts on this?  Just curious.
<br />
<br />pz!
<br />
<br />Jonathon

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


